eventDesc: Black Tech in Brum Meet up
benefitDesc: Our community offers a supportive environment for tech innovators and entrepreneurs to showcase their projects, gain exposure, and access funding options to fuel their ventures.
aboutImgDescOne: Founded by Carla Brown, a Front End Developer, UX designer, and Co-Founder of Syncd:in. Black Tech in Brum is a initiative dedicated to serving, supporting, and fostering growth within the Black Tech community in Birmingham. With a strong focus on creating new opportunities, our organisation strives to empower individuals by providing resources, networking events, and support. Together, we aim to drive innovation, diversity, and success in the vibrant tech ecosystem of Birmingham.

benefitDesc: Job seekers can leverage the resources and networking opportunities and connect with industry professionals who can provide quidance and support in their job search endeavours.
aboutImgDescTwo: Black Tech in Brum has made remarkable progress since its conception, successfully building a thriving community of over 200 individuals across various social media platforms. We have been actively hosting events that not only foster the growth of our community but also provide the essentials require. These events serve as valuable opportunities for networking. knowledge sharing, and collaboration, enabling us to collectively advance in our tech journeys.
